Title : Synoptical astrology
Text : {{Refimprove|date=April 2014}}
The theory of '''synoptical astrology''' was created by [[:hu:Orosz László Wladimir|László Wladimir Orosz]], Hungarian philosopher and astrologer.[[File:Synoptical Astrology Chart.jpg|thumb|upright|right|Synoptical Astrology Chart with equal sidereal zodiac and constellational sectors]]
[[File:Synoptical Horoscope.jpg|thumb|upright|right|Synoptical Astrology Horoscope with unequal constellational zodiac and constellational sectors]]
[[File:Dalai_Lama_XIV_synoptical_horoscope_-_Indian.jpg|thumb|upright|right|Synoptical Chartwheel - with Indian Lunar Mansions]]
[[File:Dalai_Lama_XIV_synoptical_horoscope_-_Chinese.jpg|thumb|upright|right|Synoptical Chartwheel - with Chinese Lunar Mansions]]
[[File:Dalai_Lama_XIV_synoptical_horoscope_-_Arabic.jpg|thumb|upright|right|Synoptical Chartwheel - with Arabic Lunar Mansions]]
[[File:Dalai_Lama_XIV_synoptical_horoscope_-_Scythian.jpg|thumb|upright|right|Synoptical Horoscope - Scythian/Oriental Moon Mansions]]
This synopsis  considers the [[Sidereal and tropical astrology|Tropical]] and the [[Sidereal and tropical astrology|Sidereal Zodiacs]] simultaneously with the Constellational zodiac or the real zodiacal [[Constellations]].<ref>[https://sites.google.com/site/thesignszodiac The three types of Zodiacs]</ref></blockquote>

By this approach, the tropical frame represents the destined ’earthly’ road, the personal life path and emphasizes mostly the psychic, somatic and psychosomatic elements of the nativities - in analogy with the [[Sarira|gross body]] and the [[jagrat|waking state]], the sidereal and the real constellational ones give information on the spiritual (pneumatic) relations and reveals the After Death (post mortem) Conditions - in analogy with the [[Sarira|subtle body]] and the [[svapna|dream state]]. In the sidereal frame, this school prefers the Fagan-Bradley [[ayanamsa|ayanāṃśa]] .

The Synoptical [[horoscope]] has its own unique way of drawing: we can view the tropical signs inside of the chartwheel, the Sidereal Zodiac is in the middle and the real Constellations can be found in the outermost zone.<ref>[https://sites.google.com/site/horoscopesoftware/home/inner-sky-astrology---screenshots The Synoptical Horoscope]</ref></blockquote>

Since the real constellations are unequal, Synoptical Astrology divides the sectors uniquely. To measure these unequal sectors ’dynamic degrees’ are introduced.

A constellational sector is opened by the first [[Fixed Stars|'fixed' star]] (in the direction of the planets' common moving) that is clearly belonging to the given constellation and traditionally considered so. The sector is bordered by the first 'marker' star of the next constellation. The [[ecliptic]] plane divides the sectors into northern and southern regions in some cases e. g. Aries - Taurus or Aquarius - Pisces, so, for example, a planet with northern ecliptic [[latitude]] enters the constellation of Pisces much sooner than one with southern latitude - in this system. Concerning the [[astrological aspects]], Synoptical Astrology focuses also on the [[Numerology|arithmological]] characteristics of the natural number (positive integer) which divide the circle of 360&nbsp;degrees.<ref>[http://www.inner-sky.com The Basic Elements of the Synoptical Astrology]</ref></blockquote>

The unequal constellational sectors in the Synoptical Astrology are below.
